Nanoporou sGaN coating layers deposited using Ti as catalyst have a totally different morphology, remembering the shape of a sea star. Apparently, GaN started to grow as an epitaxial layer on the substrate with a further growth of nanoporousGaNparticles on the top of it (see Fig. 5(e)). This texturation of the film, induced by the catalyst, is confirmed by the XRD pattern recorded for this sample shown in Fig. 6. The non-uniform distribution of the intensity in the Debye rings recorded with the GADDS detector (see Fig. 6(a)) and the different intensity of the diffraction peaks, indicated this texturation. However, it is not easy to establish which is the preferential orientation of the particles from the data obtained. What we observed is that the (0002), (101¯3)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
